text: Over the past fourteen weeks, gasoline retail prices have experienced a pronounced upward trend. This sustained increase has been primarily driven by a significant and steady rise in the cost of key crude oil benchmarks. Concurrently, refinery operations have faced challenges, with output periodically constrained by both planned maintenance and unexpected outages. These factors have coincided with a drawdown in gasoline inventories, indicating that supply has struggled to keep pace with robust consumer demand. The market has also contended with choppy price movements, reflecting the ongoing volatility in these fundamental drivers. Weather-related disruptions to both refining and logistics have further contributed to the market's tightness and the upward pressure on prices at the pump.
